      "url": "https://floss.social/@pottekkat/113476178211687336",
      "created_at": "2024-11-13T14:44:26.949Z",
      "content": "<p>For me, CSS is just trying every value for a property until I get what I want.</p><p>This CSS ignorance has only increased with access to Copilot in my code editor, where I conveniently delegate CSS specifics to the AI.</p><p>Today, I found this excellent interactive tutorial on CSS Flexbox (which I use a lot) that helps you intuitively understand how to use it properly.</p><p>I should look for more such CSS tutorials instead of trying random things.</p>",
