      "url": "https://floss.social/@pottekkat/113470577232955310",
      "created_at": "2024-11-12T15:00:02.797Z",
      "content": "<p>I have been using Front Matter CMS to manage my Hugo-based blog for the past month.</p><p>Spoiler: It works great!</p><p>I had tried other CMS solutions before, but every single one had annoying gaps that prevented me from committing fully.</p><p>Front Matter runs entirely in Visual Studio Code and has been a pleasant exception.</p><p>Read more on my blog: <a href=\"https://navendu.me/posts/cms-ide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://</span><span class=\"\">navendu.me/posts/cms-ide/</span><span class=\"invisible\"></span></a></p>",
