    {
      "id": "113435912546533450",
      "url": "https://floss.social/@pottekkat/113435912546533450",
      "created_at": "2024-11-06T12:04:21.659Z",
      "content": "<p>This is the simplest way to put it. SOFTWARE CAN&#39;T BE PATENTED.</p><p>While there has been an increase in software patents in India, there has also been an increase in companies adopting open source, community-friendly business models. Initiatives like End Software Patents (India) are helping discourage the former and embrace the latter.</p><p>Screenshot from &quot;Why is open-source community in India rallying against software patents&quot; by TechCircle.</p>",
      "account": {
        "id": "113236196865901581",
        "display_name": "Navendu Pottekkat",
        "username": "pottekkat",
        "acct": "pottekkat",
        "avatar": "https://cdn.masto.host/floss/accounts/avatars/113/236/196/865/901/581/original/b6c55327c77bfbf5.png"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "113435901954826656",
      "url": "https://floss.social/@pottekkat/113435901954826656",
      "created_at": "2024-11-06T12:01:40.042Z",
      "content": "<p>Read the full article by Dries Buytaert here: <a href=\"https://dri.es/balancing-makers-and-takers-to-scale-and-sustain-open-source\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://</span><span class=\"ellipsis\">dri.es/balancing-makers-and-ta</span><span class=\"invisible\">kers-to-scale-and-sustain-open-source</span></a></p>",
      "account": {
        "id": "113236196865901581",
        "display_name": "Navendu Pottekkat",
        "username": "pottekkat",
        "acct": "pottekkat",
        "avatar": "https://cdn.masto.host/floss/accounts/avatars/113/236/196/865/901/581/original/b6c55327c77bfbf5.png"
